title: Survey Finds Boys With Rigid Views Of Masculinity Are More Likely To Harm Others | 10 News+
description: A national study has highlighted the dangers that young men face if they hold onto rigid and outdated ideas of what it is to be a man. The Adolescent Man Box Survey found that boys aged between 14 and 18 who identify with hyper-masculine stereotypes are not only more miserable and lonely, but also more likely to harm others, particularly women. title: Man Collapses During White House Oval Office Press Event | 10 News
description: A man has collapsed during an Oval Office press event, with US President Donald Trump watching on.  Trump and several key health officials in his administration were announcing reduced cost weight loss drugs for Americans, which would make drugs such as Ozempic and Wegovy more accessible as a weight loss treatment. Footage from the event shows a man standing behind Eli Lilly CEO David Ricks wobbling on his feet before collapsing to the ground.  Close Trump ally Dr. Mehmet Oz attended to the man as the President rose to his feet and stood facing cameras while press were ushered out of the room. Trump later confirmed the man was being attended to and was feeling better. title: Trump Says ‘It’s Safe To Fly’ As FAA Cuts Air Traffic By 10 Per Cent Amid Shutdown | 10 News
description: Donald Trump has insisted “it’s safe to fly,” even as the FAA prepares to slash air traffic by 10 per cent across 40 major US airports amid the record-breaking government shutdown.  Speaking from the Oval Office, Trump defended the move as ensuring “100 per cent safety” for passengers, while dismissing concerns about mounting flight delays and unpaid air traffic controllers.  Transportation Secretary Sean Duffy and FAA chief Bryan Bedford said the cuts, expected to affect major hubs including New York, Washington DC, Chicago and Los Angeles, aim to reduce pressure on fatigued staff who have gone more than a month without pay.  The shutdown, now in its 36th day, has already caused widespread airport disruptions and staffing shortages.   Trump again urged Senate Republicans to scrap the filibuster rule to pass legislation and took a swipe at outgoing House Speaker Nancy Pelosi, calling her “an evil woman who did a poor job.”  Join the conversation and follow us on: Twitter: http://twitter.com/10NewsAU Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/10NewsAU/ Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/10NewsAU/ TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@10NewsAU 10 News airs at 5pm, seven nights a week in your local market on Network 10.
